<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Combo> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Combo Family" ;
    m2:genericConceptCount 5 ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-24" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "GenericConcepts produced by synergistic combination of N parent GenericConcepts (N ≥ 2) via the n-ary tensor assembly and emergence morphism (⊗ⁿ⇒). The resulting concept has semantic identity irreducible to any subset of its parents. Shared dimensions between parents are contracted via lattice join (F ⊔ F = F). Members: GenericConceptCombo (abstract pattern), Cascade, Processor, LocalActivationLateralInhibition, ButterflyEffect." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConceptFamily" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Component> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Component" ;
    m2:distinction [ ] ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Information",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Structure" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 1e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Computer system: CPU, RAM, Storage",
        "Economic system: Production, Distribution, Consumption",
        "Fire Triangle: Fuel, Oxygen, Heat (3 components)",
        "RGB color: Red, Green, Blue primaries",
        "Water molecule: 2 H atoms + 1 O atom" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Structural" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "neutral" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "S ⊗ I" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I" ;
    m2:implements <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Composable> ;
    m2:perspective "dual" ;
    m2:relationToSynergy "Components combine through Synergy (A → S → I) to create emergent whole. Removal of any component may destroy system (Fire Triangle: remove any → fire stops)." ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:transdisciplinaryValidation [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "structural_part + functional_information" ;
    rdfs:comment "Elementary constitutive part of a system with functional role in the whole. Distinguished from arbitrary partition by having meaningful function." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:Composable",
        "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Composition> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Composition (Composition/Decomposition)" ;
    m2:couplingExplanation "Structure (S) defines which parts exist and how they are arranged. Information (I) encodes the interfaces that bind parts together. Attractor (A) is the emergent outcome of the assembly — the property that 'the whole is more than the sum of its parts'. In Decomposition, S and I suffice to identify the parts, but A cannot be extracted since it is a property of the assembled whole." ;
    m2:dimensionSemantics [ ] ;
    m2:discoveryContext "Fundamental structural operation identified during TSCG framework design. The asymmetric dual nature (Composition gains A, Decomposition loses A) distinguishes it from simple bidirectional Transformation. Corrected in v15.3.2: formula split from single concatenated string 'S ⊗ I ⊗ A (composition) / S ⊗ I (decomposition)' into proper m2:polaritySemantics structure with separate pole1/pole2 formulas." ;
    m2:distinctionFromRelated [ ] ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:expression "S ⊗ I ⊗ A^{p}" ;
    m2:expressionTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes A^{p}" ;
    m2:fullName "Composition (Decomposition)" ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Attractor",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Information",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Structure" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 2.5e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Composition: Atoms → molecule (H₂ + O → H₂O)",
        "Composition: Fuel + O₂ + Heat → Flame (combustion dynamics emerge)",
        "Composition: LEGO bricks → construction (emergent form)",
        "Composition: R + G + B → Color percept (visual qualia emerges)",
        "Decomposition: Color → (R, G, B) triplet (spectral analysis)",
        "Decomposition: Construction → LEGO bricks (form lost)",
        "Decomposition: Flame → Fuel, O₂, Heat (forensics)",
        "Decomposition: Molecule → atoms (H₂O → H₂ + O)" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Structural" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "dual" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "S ⊗ I ⊗ A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I (x) A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaExpanded "Structure ⊗ Information ⊗ Attractor" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaNote "Decomposition pole: S ⊗ I — see m2:polaritySemantics" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes A (composition)" ;
    m2:perspective "dual" ;
    m2:polaritySemantics [ ] ;
    m2:poleMapping [ ] ;
    m2:shortName "Composition" ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:versionHistory [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "structural_assembly + polarity(composition|decomposition)" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-01-14" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "Bidirectional structural operation forming the fundamental duality of assembly and disassembly. Composition (bottom-up): aggregation of elementary parts into an emergent whole — the whole acquires properties (Attractor) absent from parts alone (S ⊗ I ⊗ A). Decomposition (top-down): partition of a whole into its elementary constituents — the Attractor (emergent property) dissolves, leaving only structure and interfaces (S ⊗ I). The asymmetry between the two poles is ontological: composition requires an Attractor (emergent property that justifies the assembly), while decomposition loses it." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#ConceptContract> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Concept Contract" ;
    m2:designNote "ConceptContracts are NOT GenericConcepts — they have no tensor formula. They are purely behavioral specifications. A GenericConcept may implement 0..N ConceptContracts. Current contracts: Triggerable, Observable, Composable, Stateful." ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-24" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "Abstract class defining a behavioral contract that a GenericConcept can implement. Analogous to interfaces in object-oriented programming: a ConceptContract specifies a capability or behavioral obligation without prescribing implementation. GenericConcepts implement contracts via multiple rdfs:subClassOf (mixin pattern), e.g. m2:Event rdfs:subClassOf [m2:GenericConcept, m2:Triggerable]. The m2:implements AnnotationProperty documents the intent explicitly. ConceptContracts are orthogonal to GenericConceptFamilies: a contract cuts across multiple families (Dynamic, Structural, Regulatory...) to group concepts by shared behavioral capability rather than structural similarity." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "owl:Thing" .

