<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConcept> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "M2 GenericConcept" ;
    rdfs:comment "A systemic pattern emerging from tensor product of M3 dimensions. Represents a recognizable organizational motif found across multiple domains." .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptCombo> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "GenericConceptCombo (Synergistic Combination)" ;
    m2:couplingRule [ ] ;
    m2:discoveryContext "Emerged from VSM modeling requirement: VarietyAmplification and VarietyAttenuation each combine two existing M2 genericConcepts (ValueSpace + Amplification) into a new capability that neither parent provides alone. The pattern is general - any directed synergistic fusion of multiple genericConcepts follows the same structural rule ( ⊗ ⁿ⇒). Formalized as M2 genericConcept to enable systematic instantiation in M1 domain extensions. Originally noted in TO_DO as M1 - corrected to M2 as the generic mechanism belongs at the universal pattern level, while domain-specific instances belong in M1. N-ary generalization (n ≥ 2) added 2026-02-06 to remove artificial binary restriction and enable ternary/higher-order combinations observed in complex adaptive systems." ;
    m2:distinctionFromRelated [ ] ;
    m2:formulaSemantics [ ] ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Attractor",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Information",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Structure" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 4e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "AdaptiveRegulatedLearning (n=3, hypothetical) = GenericConceptCombo(Regulation, Adaptation, Memory) - feedback-controlled learning with historical context",
        "CompositePattern (n=2, Software) = GenericConceptCombo(Modularity, Imbrication) - recursive component trees",
        "EnzymeRegulationCascade (n=2, Biology) = GenericConceptCombo(Regulation, Amplification) - gain-controlled feedback loops",
        "MonetaryPolicy (n=2, Economics) = GenericConceptCombo(ValueSpace, Amplification) - credit expansion within bounded value space",
        "RecursiveViability (n=2, M1_VSM) = GenericConceptCombo(Imbrication, Autonomy) - each nested level maintains operational independence",
        "ResilientModularEvolution (n=3, hypothetical) = GenericConceptCombo(Resilience, Modularity, Evolution) - fault-tolerant systems that adapt structure over time",
        "VarietyAmplification (n=2, M1_VSM) = GenericConceptCombo(ValueSpace, Amplification) - amplifies variety while preserving epistemic accessibility (VSM S2)",
        "VarietyAttenuation (n=2, M1_VSM) = GenericConceptCombo(ValueSpace, Amplification) - attenuates variety while maintaining verifiability (VSM S3)" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Combo" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "neutral" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "⊗ ᵢ₌₁ⁿ Mᵢ ⇒ M_result" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "(x)_i=1^n M_i => M_result" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "\\bigotimes_{i=1}^{n} M_i \\Rightarrow M_{result}" ;
    m2:mathematicalNote [ ] ;
    m2:nArityCoupling [ ] ;
    m2:perspective "map" ;
    m2:relationToCategoryTheoryMorphisms [ ] ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:transdisciplinaryValidation [ ] ;
    m2:versionHistory [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "synergistic_combination_of_genericConcepts + emergent_genericConcept + noise_reduction" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-01-31" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    dcterms:modified "2026-02-06" ;
    rdfs:comment "Parameterized genericConcept produced by synergistic combination of N parent genericConcepts (N ≥ 2) via n-ary tensor assembly and emergence morphism ( ⊗ ⁿ⇒). The result is a new genericConcept whose semantic identity cannot be reduced to any subset of parents - shared dimensions between parents create multi-way epistemic coupling rather than simple concatenation. First genericConcept in M2 whose tensor formula is structural (parameterized) rather than fixed. Most practical instances use N=2 or N=3 for tractability. Instances are domain-specific and belong to M1 extensions via functor_instantiation." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptDimensionPair> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Dimension Pair" ;
    m2:convention "p=1: dimension present (richer pole); p=0: dimension absent (A⁰=1 neutral)" ;
    m2:parametricOperator "A^{p}, p ∈ {0,1}" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-18" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "A GenericConceptPair where the two poles differ by the PRESENCE or ABSENCE of one ASFID dimension, formalized as A^p (p=1: dimension present; p=0: A⁰=1, neutral tensor element, dimension absent). The pole with p=1 has strictly more expressive power than the pole with p=0. Example: Composition (S ⊗ I ⊗ A^p): p=1 → Composition (emergent property A present), p=0 → Decomposition (A dissolved, only S ⊗ I remains)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConceptPair" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptFamily> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "GenericConcept Family" ;
    rdfs:comment "A family grouping of genericConcepts based on dominant M3 dimensions and functional role in system behavior. Renamed from Category to GenericConceptFamily to avoid confusion with Category Theory (mathematical category theory)." .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptPair> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "GenericConcept Pair" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-18" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "A genericConcept whose semantics are constituted by two named, structurally opposed poles sharing the same base tensor formula. The two poles are related by a parametric operator (p ∈ {0,1}) or by a structural reversal (direction, cardinality). Subclasses: DimensionPair (dimension present/absent via A^p), SignPair (sign reversal via (-1)^p), StructuralPair (direction or cardinality reversal). Distinct from m2:dualCounterpart which links two DIFFERENT genericConcepts (e.g. LALI ↔ ButterflyEffect sharing a parent but with different structures)." ;
    rdfs:seeAlso "m2:GenericConceptDimensionPair, m2:GenericConceptSignPair, m2:GenericConceptStructuralPair" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptSignPair> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Sign Pair" ;
    m2:convention "p=0: positive pole (enabling/amplifying); p=1: negative pole (inhibiting/attenuating)" ;
    m2:parametricOperator "(-1)^{p}, p ∈ {0,1}" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-18" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "A GenericConceptPair where the two poles differ by a SIGN REVERSAL on the base formula, formalized as (-1)^p · F(ASFID) where F is the shared base formula. p=0 → positive pole (enabling, amplifying, constructive); p=1 → negative pole (inhibiting, attenuating, destructive). Examples: Activation/Inhibition = (-1)^p (A ⊗ D); Convergence/Divergence = (-1)^p ∇·D; Synergy+/Synergy− = (-1)^p (I ⊗ D)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConceptPair" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#GenericConceptStructuralPair> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Structural Pair" ;
    m2:parametricOperator "None (structural reversal: direction or cardinality)" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-02-18" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "A GenericConceptPair where the two poles differ by a STRUCTURAL REVERSAL that cannot be reduced to a scalar parametric operator (dimension presence or sign). Two subtypes: (1) Direction reversal: same dimensions, opposite flow direction (e.g. Encoding I_src→I_coded vs Decoding I_coded→I_src). (2) Cardinality reversal: N:1 vs 1:N structural aggregation (e.g. Fusion {S₁⊗...⊗Sₙ}→S vs Fission S→{S₁⊗...⊗Sₙ}). In both cases m2:expression is replaced by explicit m2:poleMapping with pole1/pole2 formulas." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConceptPair" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Gradient> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Gradient" ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:hasAttribute [ ] ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Flow",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Information" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 2e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Concentration gradient",
        "Potential difference",
        "Temperature gradient" ;
