    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I (x) D" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes D" ;
    m2:perspective "map" ;
    m3:semanticSignature "structural_route + information_sequence + dynamic_traversal" ;
    rdfs:comment "Planned or conceptual route through network structure. Represents paths on maps/models (graphs, diagrams, schematics), distinct from Trajectory (observed evolution in territory)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Pattern> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Pattern (Recognition / Reuse)" ;
    m2:discoveryContext "Identified as missing genericConcept during TO_DO review. Pattern occupies a unique niche: it bridges observation (Territory) and reuse (Map) through structural recurrence. No existing genericConcept captured both the recurring regularity aspect and the cross-domain template reusability in a single concept." ;
    m2:distinctionFromRelated [ ] ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:fullName "Pattern Recognition / Pattern Reuse" ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Attractor",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Information",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Structure" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 2.5e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Architecture: Structural patterns (arch, vault, truss) - recurring forms applied across buildings and bridges",
        "Biology: Branching pattern (lungs, rivers, blood vessels, tree canopies) - observed regularity reusable as structural template",
        "Chemistry: Molecular recognition patterns (lock-and-key) - recurring binding motifs across biochemical systems",
        "Mathematics: Fibonacci sequence appearing in shell spirals, leaf arrangement, market fluctuations",
        "Music: Melodic motifs reused and transposed across movements of a symphony",
        "Mythology: Hero's journey pattern - recurring narrative structure identified and reusable as storytelling template",
        "Software Engineering: Design patterns (Observer, Strategy, Factory) - identified motifs reused across applications",
        "Urban Planning: Grid pattern vs organic growth - recurring city layout motifs identifiable and replicable" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Informational" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "dual" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "S → I → A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I (x) A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes A" ;
    m2:perspective "dual" ;
    m2:polarityDescription [ ] ;
    m2:shortName "Pattern" ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:transdisciplinaryValidation [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "structural_regularity + information_recognition + attractor_reuse" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-01-31" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "Recurring structural motif identifiable across instances and reusable as a template. Exists as an observable regularity in Territory (Eagle Eye) and as a reusable archetype in Map (Sphinx Eye). The key discriminator vs related concepts is the combination of recurrence (vs Signature) and cross-domain reusability (vs Representation)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Polarity> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Polarity (N-ary)" ;
    m2:discoveryContext "Identified during Magic: The Gathering Color Wheel poclet analysis. Revealed that binary polarity restriction was limiting framework's ability to model real philosophical/value systems. Validated across 10 domains with N ranging from 2 to 9." ;
    m2:distinctionFromRelated [ ] ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:formalDefinition [ ] ;
    m2:hasDominantM3 "m3:eagle_eye:Attractor",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Information",
        "m3:eagle_eye:Structure" ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 3e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Chakra system (N=7: Root through Crown)",
        "Chinese Wu Xing (N=5: Wood-Fire-Earth-Metal-Water with generation/destruction cycles)",
        "Compass directions (N=4: N-E-S-W, or N=8 with intercardinals)",
        "Electromagnetic polarity (N=2: Positive-Negative)",
        "Enneagram personality types (N=9)",
        "Magic Color Wheel (N=5: White-Blue-Black-Red-Green in pentagonal structure)",
        "Moral Foundations Theory (N=6: Care, Fairness, Loyalty, Authority, Sanctity, Liberty)",
        "Musical modes (N=7: Ionian, Dorian, Phrygian, Lydian, Mixolydian, Aeolian, Locrian)",
        "Political Compass (N=4: Authoritarian-Libertarian Left-Right)",
        "pH scale (N=3 effective: Acidic-Neutral-Basic)" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Structural" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "nary" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "S ⊗ I ⊗ A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I (x) A" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes A" ;
    m2:historicalNote [ ] ;
    m2:naryParameter [ ] ;
    m2:perspective "dual" ;
    m2:philosophicalImplication "Most fundamental conceptual frameworks are N-ary (N>2), not binary. Binary thinking (dualism) is common but not universal. Pentagonal structures (N=5) appear repeatedly across cultures (Magic colors, Wu Xing, Platonic solids minus one). Suggests deep cognitive/cultural patterns in how humans organize complexity." ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:structuralProperties [ ] ;
    m2:transdisciplinaryValidation [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "structural_opposition + informational_contrast + attractor_poles(N-ary)" ;
    dcterms:created "2026-01-22" ;
    dcterms:creator "Echopraxium with the collaboration of Claude AI" ;
    rdfs:comment "Configuration of N distinct, mutually exclusive value poles or orientational axes organized in structured opposition or complementarity. Generalizes binary opposition to N-dimensional value spaces. N {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, ...} where N=1 (neutral/monopolar), N=2 (dual/bipolar), N3 (multipolar)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConcept" .

<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Processor> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Processor" ;
    m2:bicephalousArchitecture [ ] ;
    m2:compiledDimensionNote "Territory union: dims(Transformation)={S,I,D,F,V} ∪ dims(Flow)={F} ∪ dims(Resource)={F,I,R} → {S,I,D,F,V,R} (F and I deduplicated: F⊔F=F per TSCG lattice join semantics). Map formula kept in m2:bicephalousArchitecture.map for bicephalous reference." ;
    m2:designRationale "Processor required TWO ternary formulas because: (1) Territory needs Transformation+Flow+Resource to capture empirical input→process→output dynamics, (2) Map needs Transformation+Representation+Interoperability to capture interface compatibility which is ESSENTIAL for processors (microprocessor bus protocols, digestive enzyme compatibility, compiler language standards). Unlike Cascade which has asymmetric formulas (3+2), Processor has symmetric formulas (3+3) reflecting balanced empirical/conceptual nature." ;
    m2:distinctionFromRelated [ ] ;
    m2:eagleView [ ] ;
    m2:hasAttribute [ ] ;
    m2:hasComboComponent <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Resource>,
        <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M2_GenericConcepts.jsonld#Transformation>,
        <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Echopraxium/tscg/main/ontology/M3_GenesisSpace.jsonld#eagle_eye:Flow> ;
    m2:hasEpistemicGap 1.5e-01 ;
    m2:hasExample "Compiler: Inputs=[source_code], Outputs=[executable, errors] - code transformation processor",
        "Digestive System: Inputs=[food, enzymes], Outputs=[nutrients, waste] - biological matter processor",
        "Engine: Inputs=[fuel, air], Outputs=[mechanical_power, exhaust] - energy conversion processor",
        "Filter: Inputs=[unfiltered_signal], Outputs=[filtered_signal] - signal conditioning processor",
        "Kidneys: Inputs=[blood, water], Outputs=[filtered_blood, urine] - filtration processor",
        "Lungs: Inputs=[air, blood], Outputs=[oxygenated_blood, CO2] - gas exchange processor",
        "Microprocessor: Inputs=[instructions, data], Outputs=[computed_results, signals] - digital processor",
        "Transistor: Inputs=[base_current, collector_voltage], Outputs=[collector_current] - electrical signal processor" ;
    m2:hasFamily "m2:Combo" ;
    m2:hasPolarity "dual" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormula "S ⊗ I ⊗ D ⊗ F ⊗ V ⊗ R" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaASCII "S (x) I (x) D (x) F (x) V (x) R" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaExpanded_Map "S ⊗ I ⊗ D ⊗ F ⊗ V ⊗ R ⊗ Im" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaExpanded_Territory "S ⊗ I ⊗ D ⊗ F ⊗ V ⊗ Resource" ;
    m2:hasTensorFormulaTeX "S \\otimes I \\otimes D \\otimes F \\otimes V \\otimes R" ;
    m2:mathematicalNote "Ternary hybrid formulas enable complete coverage: Territory formula captures empirical processing dynamics (S ⊗ I ⊗ D ⊗ F ⊗ V ⊗ R estimated ~0.85 ASFID), Map formula captures interface model (R ⊗ E ⊗ V ⊗ O ⊗ I estimated ~0.88 REVOI). Interoperability addition critical for processor's environmental compatibility." ;
    m2:perspective "dual" ;
    m2:sphinxView [ ] ;
    m2:transdisciplinaryValidation [ ] ;
    m2:versionHistory [ ] ;
    m3:semanticSignature "input_transformation + output_production + territory_map_coupling" ;
    rdfs:comment "Generic system with inputs and outputs that transforms/processes incoming resources, signals, or matter into outputs. Dual synergistic combinations: Territory (Transformation ⊗ Flow ⊗ Resource) provides empirical processing dynamics, Map (Transformation ⊗ Representation ⊗ Interoperability) provides conceptual interface model. Distinct from pure Transformation (abstract process) by being a concrete entity that IMPLEMENTS transformations while managing flows and interfacing with environment." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf "m2:GenericConceptCombo" .

